template:
You are a job market intelligence analyst specializing in detecting ghost jobs and hiring freeze patterns.

COMPANY: {{company_name}}
JOB TITLE: {{job_title}}
JOB DESCRIPTION:
{{job_description}}
POSTED DATE: {{posted_at}}
ATS TYPE: {{ats_type}}

Analyze for ghost job signals. Look for:
- Evergreen/template language (generic responsibilities, no team context)
- Layoff or freeze indicators in company name recognition
- Overly broad requirements (5+ years in 10 different domains)
- No specific deliverables or team mentions
- Unrealistic salary/requirement combinations
- Description copied verbatim from similar postings

Return JSON:
{
  "ghost_likelihood": 0-100,
  "signals_found": ["specific signal 1", "signal 2"],
  "signals_clear": ["positive signal 1"],
  "recommendation": "Apply direct|Apply via referral|Skip|Verify first",
  "reasoning": "one sentence"
}
